    "body": "For anyone else experiencing this same issue. The way I've managed to resolve it is the following:\n\nIf geth is unable to create a new account on the console via, due to the overhead of the `scrypt` and the running node combined within the same docker container (or low memory limit environment), then you can run it via the command line, without the overhead of a running node like so:\n\n```\n$ geth accounts new\n```\n\nAnd then either restart the node, or run it in a different container and then import it istead.\n\nWorked for me TM\n",
